## Code Architecture Summary: Onboarding Flow

Based on my analysis of the codebase, here's how the current flow works and where the key pieces are:

---

### 1. **Main Orchestrator Page**
**File:** `/Users/aryan/Projects/GAIA/gaia-onboarding-revamp/apps/web/src/app/[locale]/(main)/onboarding/page.tsx`

**Lines 81–98:** Stage-to-content mapping
```typescript
const stageContent = (() => {
  switch (stage) {
    case "revealTodos":
      return <RevealTodos state={state} dispatch={dispatch} />;
    case "workflows":
      return <Workflows state={state} dispatch={dispatch} />;
    case "platforms":
      return <Platforms state={state} dispatch={dispatch} />;
    case "chat":
      return <Chat state={state} chat={chat} />;
  }
})();
```

**Lines 100–119:** Composer mapping (input at bottom)
```typescript
const composer = (() => {
  switch (stage) {
    case "revealTodos":
      return null;  // No input
    case "workflows":
      return <WorkflowsComposer state={state} dispatch={dispatch} />;
    case "platforms":
      return null;  // No input
    case "chat":
      return <ChatComposer state={state} />;  // Chat input
  }
})();
```

**Key insight:** When `stage === "chat"`, `stageContent` renders `<Chat>` component and `composer` renders `<ChatComposer>`. Both are shown simultaneously.

